cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
title: "Serving a Fine-Tuned Qwen3.5-27B (Dense, NVFP4) on DGX Spark"
abstract: >-
  Reproducible guide and toolchain for quantizing a DoRA fine-tuned
  Qwen3.5-27B dense model to NVFP4 via nvidia-modelopt and serving it on a
  single NVIDIA DGX Spark (GB10, SM121) using native vLLM. Documents the
  post-export fixes required by modelopt 0.42 (use of
  export_hf_checkpoint() in place of save_pretrained(), MTP weight grafting,
  VLM wrapper config rewrite, safetensors index generation), Multi-Token
  Prediction speculative decoding setup, and a blind-scored quality
  shootout across three serving stacks (vLLM NVFP4, llama.cpp GGUF
  Q4_K_M / Q5_K_M+imatrix) and three architectures (Qwen3.5-27B dense,
  Qwen3.5-35B-A3B MoE, Gemma 4 26B-A4B). Baseline: 11.2 tok/s; with MTP:
  17.1 tok/s (+52%).
